paddock sheep
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a sheep grazed on fenced flat and down country [as opposed to hill sheep that are grazed on hills and high country.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
