Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: As to the third, I believe it would be a great gain to the West Coast, but as our Bishop, according to his speeches, is better acquainted with the larger towns and cities than with the country, I may point out that the long woolled paddock sheep require much more care and supervision to prevent them getting "cast" and breaking fences, than the hardy short woolled sheep of the ranges, and therefore we want a young energetic man more than others under different conditions.
